<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Turbocharger - Removal</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Removal</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="13">
            <title>Standard Torque Turbocharger</title>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figF15/F1516.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="532px"/>
                <caption>Removing Road Draft Tube Mounting Bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Road Draft Tube Mounting Bolts (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Road Draft Tube</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two bolts securing the road draft tube to the crankcase. Relocate road draft
                    tube to gain access to the left side of the engine.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200206" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8017.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Removing Air Inlet Elbow</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Air Inlet Elbow Clamp</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Air Inlet Elbow</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase Breather</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Road Draft Tube</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the air inlet elbow clamp and remove the air inlet elbow from the turbocharger.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove exhaust pipe between the turbocharger and the muffler.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figf15/F1503A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="592px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Removing Turbocharger Air Charging Tube/Crossover Pipe Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Compressor Outlet Seal</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Compressor Outlet Clamp</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Charge Air Cooling Tube / Crossover Pipe Assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Intake Manifold Hose</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Hose Clamp(s)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the turbocharger charge air cooling tube/crossover pipe as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen the four hose clamps (two per side) that secure the hoses to the air intake
                        covers. The clamps are located on the manifold hoses.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen the turbocharger compressor outlet clamp that secures the charge air cooling
                        tube to the turbocharger compressor housing.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the charge air cooling tube/crossover pipe assembly.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the turbocharger outlet seal from the compressor housing.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Place protective caps onto the air intake manifolds.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <figure figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figF15/F1520.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="532px" box="no"/>
                <caption>EBP Wiring Harness Connection</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Wiring Harness Clip</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">EBP Wiring Harness Connector</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the EBP electrical connector from the wiring harness, if equipped.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3379.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="392px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Removing Turbocharger From Inlet Adapter, Late 1997 Model Year Engine Without Exhaust Bellows
                    Feature Shown
                </caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Compressor Housing</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Retaining Bolts (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Gasket</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Inlet Adapter</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Studs On Inlet Adapter (2)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Late 1997 Model Year, Engines Without Exhaust Bellows Feature: Remove two retaining
                    bolts and the two retaining nuts at the exhaust inlet adapter to the turbine housing flange. Save
                    these two retaining bolts. They will be reused in the assembly procedure. Discard the two retaining
                    nuts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Late 1997 Model Year, Engines With Exhaust Bellows Feature: Remove four retaining bolts
                    at the exhaust inlet adapter to the turbine housing flange. Save these four retaining bolts. They
                    will be reused in the assembly procedure.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figf15/F1523.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Removing Exhaust Inlet Adapter from Turbocharger, Engine With Exhaust Bellows Feature Shown
                    (1998 through 2003 Model Years)
                </caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Inlet Adapter</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Clamp</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and save turbocharger V-band clamp. Remove seal, if equipped.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2050202" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1537.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Disconnecting EBP Piston Rod (1998 through 2003 Model Years)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">EBP Piston Rod</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Control Arm</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Slide Lock</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Move the slide lock back and disconnect the EBP piston rod from the control arm.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Late 1997 Model Year Only:Remove the bolts securing the pedestal to the crankcase.
                    Remove the turbocharger and pedestal assembly from the engine.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figf15/F1524.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Removing Turbocharger Mounting Bolts (1998 through 2003 Model Years)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">1998 through 2003 Model Years: Remove and save the two turbocharger mounting bolts.
                    Remove turbocharger from the pedestal by lifting the turbocharger up.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figeg7/EG7439.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Removing Pedestal and O-rings (1998 through 2003 Model Years)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting Bolts</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Supply and Oil Drain O-rings</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">1998 through 2003 Model Years: Remove the oil supply and oil drain O-rings from the
                    pedestal. Remove four mounting bolts securing the pedestal to the crankcase and remove the pedestal
                    from the engine.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200213" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3303.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Turbocharger Oil Supply and Oil Drain Ports</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Supply O-Ring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Drain O-Ring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Mounting Pad</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove and discard the two O-rings located on the turbocharger mounting pad. Cover
                    openings after removal.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200215" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figF15/F1507.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Turbocharger Openings to be Capped (Late 1997 Model Year Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Outlet</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Exhaust Inlet</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Oil Inlet and Oil Drain Ports</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Air Inlet</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Air Outlet</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Cap all turbocharger openings to prevent contamination. If plastic caps are not
                    available, use duct tape to cover openings.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8028A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="532px"/>
                <caption>Removing Right Exhaust Tube Mounting Hardware at Exhaust Manifold</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Right Exhaust Tube</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Tube Bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Nut</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Right Exhaust Manifold</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two nuts and bolts from right exhaust manifold. These bolts secure the right
                    exhaust tube to the exhaust manifold.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8028B.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="532px"/>
                <caption>Removing Left Exhaust Tube Mounting Hardware at Exhaust Manifold</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Left Exhaust Tube</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Tube Bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Left Exhaust Manifold</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Nut</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two nuts and bolts from left exhaust manifold. These bolts secure the left
                    exhaust tube to the exhaust manifold.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the turbocharger exhaust tube assembly from the engine.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
